-- Carlyle-backed Axalta Coating Systems files for IPO
-- 
-- Wed Aug 20, 2014 05:19PM EDT
-- None



Aug 20 (Reuters) - Buyout firm Carlyle Group LP <CG.O> backed performance coatings company Axalta Coating Systems Ltd filed with U.S. regulators on Wednesday to raise up to $100 million in an initial public offering of common stock.

The company listed Citigroup, Goldman Sachs, Deutsche Bank and JP Morgan among the underwriters for the IPO.  (http://bit.ly/1wa9s6z)